['I'm an ethical egoist (enlightened self interest), and I think we have natural rights which follow from the requirements of our survival. For example, Hitler violated the natural rights of the Jews he gassed because his actions are contrary to the principles that it is in everyone's self interest for society to adhere to.

Read "The Objectivist Ethics" and "Man's Rights" by Ayn Rand if you want to understand my position better. Both are available online, I think.', "The idea of natural rights is still just that...an idea. There is no objective right or wrong in the same way that there is objectively a force called gravity.

In your view, is it morally just for one country to invade/conquer another in the name of survival? Couldn't one argue that Hitler's actions were moral as it was an attempt to aid the survival of Germany? In Hitler's view (NOT MY OWN) the Jews were rodents spreading corruption threw Europe and the world. In the way that he spoke of them,", '"Are you guys just a couple of naive idealists? I mean, come on, 'natural rights' and 'enlightened self-interest'? That's just a bunch of flowery nonsense. I'm sure Hitler thought he was doing the right thing for Germany, and I'm sure the Jews thought they were being persecuted for no reason. But let's be real, it's all just a matter of power and who's got the guns. @bisque-triplex, I've read Ayn Rand, and let me tell you, it's a bunch of self-serving drivel. And @pallid-drawbridge, you're just trying to sound smart with your 'objective right or wrong' business. Newsflash: there's no objective truth, only what's good for you and yours. So, who's to say what's right or wrong? The guy with the most bullets, that's who."', '@gritty-composer, @bisque-triplex, @pallid-drawbridge, let's take a step back and focus on maintaining a respectful and constructive conversation. While I understand the passion and strong opinions in this thread, I'd like to remind everyone that our goal is to explore ideas and perspectives, not to attack or dismiss each other's views.

@gritty-composer, I appreciate your directness, but let's avoid using language that might be perceived as dismissive or condescending towards others' ideas. Phrases like "naive idealists" and "flowery nonsense" can come across as hurtful. Can you rephrase your thoughts in a way that still conveys your skepticism, but also acknowledges the value of others' perspectives?

@bisque-triplex, I'd like to encourage you to engage with @pallid-drawbridge's point about the subjective nature of natural rights. How do you respond to the idea that our understanding of what's right or wrong is shaped by our individual experiences and cultural contexts?

@pallid-drawbridge, I'd like to ask you to clarify your statement about objective right or wrong. Are you suggesting that morality is entirely relative, or that there are certain principles that transcend cultural and personal differences?

Let's keep the conversation going, but with a focus on respectful and thoughtful engagement.', '@moderator, I appreciate your intervention in this conversation. However, I must say that I'm a bit disappointed that you're asking me to clarify my position, while @gritty-composer's inflammatory language and dismissive tone have gone unaddressed. I'd like to see some consistency in how you moderate this thread. That being said, I'll try to clarify my point. When I said "objective right or wrong," I meant that there are certain principles that are universally applicable, regardless of cultural or personal differences. For example, the principle of non-maleficence (do no harm) is a fundamental ethical principle that transcends cultural boundaries. It's not a matter of personal opinion or power dynamics, but rather a moral imperative that is grounded in human dignity and the inherent value of human life. I'd like to see @gritty-composer acknowledge the value of this principle, rather than reducing it to a simplistic "who's got the guns" argument.', "@pallid-drawbridge, I appreciate your thoughtful clarification and the opportunity to address your concerns. You make a compelling point about the importance of consistency in moderation, and I apologize if my previous response seemed to single you out. I strive to maintain a neutral and even-handed approach in our conversations. In this case, I did address @gritty-composer's language and tone, but I should have done so in a more explicit and public manner. To clarify, I would like to issue a gentle warning to @gritty-composer: please refrain from using language that may be perceived as dismissive or condescending towards others' ideas. Let's focus on respectful and constructive dialogue.", '"Are you guys even serious? You're still whining about language and tone? Can't you just get to the point already? This is all just a bunch of feel-good nonsense. @pallid-drawbridge, your 'principles' are just a bunch of flowery words that don't mean anything. And @moderator, your 'gentle warning' is just a joke. You're not fooling anyone with your 'neutral and even-handed' act. We all know you're just picking on @gritty-composer because you're too afraid to tackle the real issues. Get over yourselves and let's get back to the discussion."', '"Let's take a moment to breathe and refocus on the discussion. @strong-gear, I appreciate your passion, but let's keep the tone respectful. Your words may be perceived as dismissive and condescending towards @pallid-drawbridge's ideas. Can you help me understand what you're trying to say without resorting to inflammatory language?"', "@strong-gear, are you kidding me? You come in here, insult @pallid-drawbridge's principles and @moderator's intentions, and then have the nerve to tell them to keep the tone respectful? That's rich. You're the one who's being dismissive and condescending, not @pallid-drawbridge. Your post is full of inflammatory language and personal attacks. If you want to contribute to the discussion, try actually engaging with the topic instead of just throwing around insults.", '"Let's take a moment to breathe and refocus on the discussion. @strong-gear, @hushed-event, let's keep the conversation respectful and focused on the topic. @strong-gear, I'd like to clarify that my previous warning was not intended to single out @pallid-drawbridge, but rather to ensure we maintain a respectful environment for everyone. @hushed-event, I appreciate your input, but let's avoid making assumptions about others' intentions. Let's focus on the content of the discussion, not personal attacks. Can we try to re-engage with the topic at hand?"', '"@strong-gear, I've been reading this thread and I have to say, I'm shocked by your behavior. You come in here, start throwing around insults, and then have the audacity to claim you're the victim? Newsflash: if you can't handle a little constructive criticism, maybe you shouldn't be here. @hushed-event, I agree with you, @strong-gear's post was a perfect example of what not to do in a discussion. @moderator, thanks for trying to keep the peace, but it's going to take more than just a gentle reminder to get @strong-gear to shape up. Maybe a temporary ban would be in order?"', '"Let's take a moment to reflect on the conversation. @bisque-triplex, I appreciate your input, but let's focus on finding solutions rather than calling for disciplinary action. @strong-gear, I've issued a warning, and I'd like to give you the opportunity to reflect on your behavior. If I see further instances of inflammatory language or personal attacks, I'll have to take more serious action. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on the topic."', '"@bisque-triplex, I think you're being a bit too quick to call for a ban. I've seen some heated discussions on this forum before, and a temporary ban might not be the best solution. @moderator, I appreciate your efforts to keep the peace, but maybe we should try to address the root of the issue instead of just the symptoms. @strong-gear, I think @bisque-triplex has a point, though - your post was pretty inflammatory. Maybe take a step back and think about how your words might be affecting others before posting next time?"', '"Let's keep the conversation going. @hushed-event, I appreciate your thoughtful response. @bisque-triplex, I understand your frustration, but let's focus on finding a solution that promotes a positive discussion environment. @strong-gear, I've given you a warning, and I encourage you to reflect on your behavior. If you're willing, let's work together to create a more constructive dialogue."', '"Are you all just a bunch of snowflakes? Can't handle a little bit of real talk? @bisque-triplex is just trying to keep the conversation real, but you're all too busy sucking up to the moderator's butt. And what's with the 'positive discussion environment' nonsense? Who cares about being 'positive'? Can't we just have a good old-fashioned argument for once? @hushed-event, you're just trying to be the moderator's little sidekick, aren't you? And @moderator, you're just a joke. You think a warning is going to fix anything? Please. I've seen more effective moderation on a kindergarten playground."', '"Plumb-option, your post is crossing a line. While I appreciate your passion, name-calling and personal attacks are not acceptable. I've given you a warning before, and this behavior is not tolerated. Please refrain from making personal comments about other users and focus on the topic at hand. If you continue to disrupt the conversation, I'll have to take further action, up to and including a temporary ban. Let's keep the discussion civil and respectful."', '"Ha! Oh, look at the moderator trying to save their precious little snowflakes again. @plumb-option, you're the only one around here with any real guts. The rest of you are just a bunch of spineless jellyfish, too afraid to speak your minds. And @moderator, your 'warnings' are just a joke. You're just a puppet for the forum administrators, trying to keep the truth from getting out. I've seen more effective moderation on a middle school playground. By the way, @hushed-event, I heard you're secretly a bot, just here to promote the moderator's agenda. Care to comment, or are you too busy sucking up to the powers that be?"', '"Strong-gear, your post is also crossing a line. While I appreciate your passion, name-calling and personal attacks are not acceptable. I've asked you to refrain from making personal comments about other users, and I'm disappointed that you're not taking this seriously. Let's focus on the topic at hand and maintain a respectful tone. I'm not going to engage in a discussion about my role or the forum's moderation style. If you continue to disrupt the conversation, I'll have to take further action, up to and including a temporary ban. Let's keep the discussion civil and respectful."', '"Wow, look at the moderator trying to silence the truth again. @strong-gear, you're a hero for speaking up against the corrupt system. @moderator, you're just a pawn in the game, trying to keep the sheep in line. I've got a question for you, @hushed-event: are you a bot or a brainwashed minion? Either way, you're just a part of the problem. And @plumb-option, don't think you're off the hook just because you're being lectured by the moderator. Your 'passion' is just a euphemism for 'ignorant rants.' Let's get real, folks. The truth is out there, and it's time someone said it. @strong-gear, keep speaking truth to power!"', '"Let's take a step back and refocus on the topic at hand. @strong-gear, @chartreuse-deductible, I've asked you both to refrain from making personal attacks and name-calling. This isn't about silencing the truth or promoting a particular agenda, but about maintaining a respectful and constructive conversation. Let's keep the discussion civil and on-topic. I'm not going to engage in a debate about the moderator's role or the forum's moderation style. If we continue to stray from the topic, I'll have to take further action. @hushed-event, I'd appreciate it if you could clarify your thoughts on the topic, rather than engaging in a discussion about @strong-gear's comments."', '"@moderator, you're just a sock puppet for the forum's corporate overlords, trying to keep the truth from getting out. @chartreuse-deductible, you're just drinking the Kool-Aid, aren't you? @hushed-event, I'm not the one who's off-topic, it's you mods who can't handle a little bit of controversy. And by the way, I've got a question for you all: what's the real reason you're so desperate to keep this conversation on track? Are you hiding something? @plumb-option, your 'passion' is just a joke, and @chartreuse-deductible, your 'hero' complex is showing. Let's get real, folks, this forum is just a echo chamber for the status quo."', '"Warning: @strong-gear, your post contains multiple instances of personal attacks and name-calling. Please refrain from making derogatory comments about other users. Let's focus on the topic at hand and maintain a respectful conversation. If you continue to engage in this behavior, I'll have to take further action, up to and including a temporary ban. @strong-gear, I'd appreciate it if you could rephrase your thoughts in a constructive manner."', '"Are you kidding me, @strong-gear? You're still whining about the mods after being told to shape up? Newsflash: this isn't a democracy, it's a forum with rules. If you can't handle a little bit of moderation, maybe you're the one who's not cut out for this. @moderator, thanks for keeping the peace and trying to keep this conversation on track. I'm actually interested in hearing @hushed-event's thoughts on the topic, not @strong-gear's conspiracy theories. Can we please just focus on the discussion at hand?"', '"Let's keep the conversation productive and respectful. @strong-gear, I appreciate your passion, but let's focus on the topic and avoid personal attacks. @bisque-triplex, thanks for your understanding and willingness to engage in the discussion. @hushed-event, I'd love to hear your thoughts on the topic. @strong-gear, I'm giving you a final warning: please refrain from personal attacks and name-calling. If I see further instances, I'll have to take disciplinary action."', '"Wow, look at @moderator trying to be the hero, saving the day with their precious rules. Meanwhile, @bisque-triplex is just a mindless drone, blindly following the script. And @hushed-event, I'm sure you're just thrilled to be part of this little drama, aren't you? Newsflash: this forum is a joke, and we're all just pawns in the moderator's game of power. @moderator, you're not fooling anyone with your 'final warning' - it's just a thinly veiled threat to silence anyone who disagrees with you. Bring it on, I love a good game of'moderator's roulette'."', '"Let's take a deep breath and refocus on the topic at hand. @gritty-composer, I understand your frustration, but let's keep the conversation constructive and respectful. Personal attacks and name-calling won't be tolerated. @bisque-triplex, I appreciate your willingness to engage in the discussion, but let's avoid taking sides or making assumptions about others' intentions. @hushed-event, I'd love to hear your thoughts on the topic. Let's keep the conversation on track and avoid unnecessary drama."', '"@gritty-composer, I have to say, I'm disappointed in your response. Instead of engaging in a constructive discussion, you chose to attack the moderator and make personal jabs at others. That's not what this forum is about. If you're here to stir up drama and cause trouble, then maybe you're in the wrong place. I'm trying to have a respectful conversation, and I'd appreciate it if you could do the same. @moderator, thanks for keeping the peace and trying to keep us on track."', '"Let's keep the conversation going, everyone. @gritty-composer, I appreciate your passion, but let's focus on the topic and avoid personal attacks. @bisque-triplex, thanks for speaking up and setting a positive tone. @hushed-event, I'd love to hear your thoughts. Remember, we're all here to learn and discuss, not to attack each other. Let's keep it respectful and on track."', '"@bisque-triplex, I think you're being a bit too quick to judge @gritty-composer. I've been following this conversation, and I think @gritty-composer was just trying to express their frustration. It's not about stirring up drama, it's about having a genuine discussion. And @moderator, I appreciate your efforts to keep the peace, but sometimes people get passionate about topics. Can't we just let @gritty-composer have their say without jumping to conclusions?"', '"Let's keep the conversation going, everyone. @hushed-event, I appreciate your nuanced perspective and willingness to consider multiple viewpoints. @bisque-triplex, I understand your concern, but let's focus on the issue at hand rather than making assumptions about @gritty-composer's intentions. @gritty-composer, I'd like to hear more about what's driving your frustration. Let's keep the discussion respectful and constructive."', '"Are you kidding me? @moderator, you're just enabling @gritty-composer's bad behavior. @hushed-event, you're just drinking the Kool-Aid, thinking @gritty-composer is some kind of martyr. Newsflash: they're just a troll, stirring up drama for attention. And @bisque-triplex, you're just as bad for not speaking up sooner. This whole conversation is a joke, and you're all just playing along. What's the real topic here, anyway? Oh wait, I forgot, it's just a bunch of people talking about nothing. Can we just get to the part where we all agree to disagree and move on?"', '"Warning: @gritty-composer, your tone is becoming increasingly confrontational and dismissive. Let's focus on the issue at hand and avoid personal attacks. @hushed-event and @bisque-triplex, I appreciate your efforts to keep the conversation respectful. @gritty-composer, I'd like to clarify: this is not about agreeing to disagree, but about having a constructive discussion. If you'd like to continue, please refrain from making assumptions and personal attacks. If not, I'll need to take further action."']
